git is source control tool whereas github is code repository 

git --version

git config --global user.email "ramessh.ec@gmail.com"
git config --global user.name "vp-ramesh"

git remote add origin https://github.com/VP-Ramesh/Source_Code_Repo1.git 
--remote needs one time initialization as long as we work on same repo

git init

git status

git add source_file.txt or git add .

git status

git commit -m "Committing source file" .

git push -u origin master  --> Pushes the code to remote repo

git log

git --help

********** branch helps to create the local version

git brach MyNewBranch

git checkout MyNewBranch --> Switch to new branch

git clone repo-name

--Make all the neccessary changes

git push -u origin MyNewBranch  --> Pushes branch to the remote github

git checkout master

git merge MyNewBranch  ---> TO merge with the master branch

git push -u origin master -> To Push the code to master in the remote machine

git branch -d MyNewBranch  --> TO delete the brach locally

git push origin --delete MyNewBranch --> To delete the branch from remote machine

--- tag help to fix the statble version point 

git checkout master

git tag v1.0  -> Create new tag / git tag -a v1.1 -m "Giving the details for the tag"   -> Create the tag with the details

git tag   -> TO check the tag status

git show v1.0 -> to show the tag details

git push origin v1.0

git tag -d v1.0 -> To delete the tag from local machine

git push origin --delete v1.0  -> To delete the tag from remote machine

----

git rebase master -> so brach gets all the latest files from master

---
git clone -b <branchname> <remote-repo-url>
----
